<HEAD>10 Killed In Road Collision Outside Bangkok</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BANGKOK, Thailand (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A pickup truck carrying tourists
collided with a truck about 120 miles southeast of Bangkok, killing
10 people, police said today.
   The accident occurred Friday as the passengers in the pickup
truck were returning from a sightseeing trip in Rayong on the Gulf
of Thailand, said Sub. Lt. Pumin Singhasut.
   Pumin said nine of the dead were in the pickup truck and that the
10th victim was a woman who was buying goods near the scene of the
crash.
   Cause of the crash was not immediately known. Pumin said the
driver of the 10-wheel truck fled the scene.
