<FIRST>r i PM-Pakistan     03-18 0123</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Pakistan,0121</SECOND>
<HEAD>Gunmen Kill 12 People In Pakistan</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KARACHI, Pakistan (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Gunmen driving through a working-class
neighborhood in Pakistan's largest city today sprayed the streets
with gunfire, killing 12 people and wounding one in apparently
random attacks.
   Witnesses said the gunmen cruising in a car opened fire in five
locations in the Malir district in western Karachi.
   Police and soldiers in vehicles mounted with machine guns swiftly
converged on the district, which is near the international airport,
but the unidentified gunmen escaped, police said.
   The violence brought to 18 the number of people killed by
marauding gunmen in cars or on motorcycles in this seaport since
March 9. Police officials said they don't know who is responsible or
what motivates them.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
