<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--DeathSentence     03-18 0138</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Death Sentence,0142</SECOND>
<HEAD>Two Sentenced To Death For Attacking Japanese</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two men were sentenced to death Saturday for
killing one visiting Japanese businessman and robbing another, the
official Xinhua News Agency said.
   Shanghai Intermediate People's Court convicted unemployed actor
Zhu Wenbo of smothering Koji Kobayashi in July in the victim's hotel
room, Xinhua said. Earlier reports said Zhu, 43, stole $545 worth of
Chinese currency from Kobayashi to cover gambling debts.
   The court also convicted 23-year-old Wu Guilong of robbing Yasuo
Kishiyo at knifepoint in October and taking nearly $1,000, Xinhua
said.
   Both attacks occurred in the Jinjiang Hotel, one of Shanghai's
best-known for foreigners.
   In the few previous cases of foreigners being slain in China,
those convicted also have been given the death penalty of a bullet
to the back of the head.
