<HEAD>Mother Being Held Hostage Sends Note For Help With Son To School</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A woman being held hostage in her apartment by
her ex-boyfriend, who was armed with a gun and a grenade, sent her
6-year-old son to school with a note asking his teacher for help.
   Police rescued Sandra Lewis and arrested the gunman with their
own ruse: a detective posing as the school principal called the
house saying the first-grader was sick and needed to be picked up.
   When Ms. Lewis and Charles Scott walked out of the apartment
Friday, 25 police officers arrested Scott without a struggle. Inside
the apartment, police found a 9mm gun, ammunition and marijuana.
   Scott was charged with unlawful imprisonment, menacing and
possession of the weapons and drugs, Capt. Joseph Hardiman said.
Police said Scott entered Ms. Lewis' apartment Thursday afternoon,
apparently angry over an assalt charge she had filed against him on
Feb. 11.
