<FIRST>r i AM-Brazil-Crash     03-18 0162</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Brazil-Crash,0166</SECOND>
<HEAD>Twin-Engine Plane Crashes In Brazil, Three Killed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>RIO DE JANEIRO, Brazil (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A twin-engine plane crashed and
exploded at an airport when it tried to avoid another aircraft while
landing, an official said. All three people aboard the plane were
reported killed.
   The private King-Air plane was landing at an airport in
southeastern Brazil when the pilot saw the second aircraft taxiing
on the same runway, airport spokesman Pulcimar Agusta said in a
telephone interview.
   Pilot Roberto Goncalves radioed the second pilot and tried to
take off again, but the plane flipped over, Agusta said. The
accident occurred in Juiz de Fora, 135 miles northwest of Rio de
Janeiro.
   ``The plane burst into flames and exploded moments after it
crashed,'' Agusta said. ``All that was left was ashes.''
   In addition to the pilot, the crash killed Ronaldo Carneiro da
Rocha and his wife Elizabeth, both Brazilians, the spokesman said.
   The plane was arriving on a flight from Rio.
