<HEAD>Man Arrested After Asking Police For Fingerprints</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FRANKLIN, Pa. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man who called police for an appointment
to be fingerprinted for his new security job was arrested instead
when officers spotted his name on a list of people with outstanding
felony warrants.
   Dana T. Myers showed up for his appointment Wednesday and was
surprised ``to say the least,'' said police dispatcher Bob Jamison.
   District Justice Robert Billingsley arraigned Myers on a warrant
from Alabama accusing him of a felony-level theft. Additional
details were unavailable. A hearing was set for May.
   Myers, 28, a former resident of Lake Charles, La., who now lives
in Exton, remained in the Venango County Jail on Saturday in lieu of
$5,000 bond.
