<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Indonesia-Boat     03-18 0132</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Indonesia-Boat,0138</SECOND>
<HEAD>Boat Sinks Off Indonesian Province, Eight Die</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JAKARTA, Indonesia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An crowded boat sank off Sulawesi
island, drowning at least eight people, a newspaper reported
Saturday.
   Rescuers saved nine people and were searching for 23 others, the
daily Suara Pembaruan reported.
   It said the vessel, which had a capacity of 20 passengers, was
packed with 40 people when it sank Friday evening three miles off
the coast and about 950 miles east of Jakarta.
   Suara Pembaruan did not name the boat or give its size.
   The accident occurred when rough waves rocked the boat as its
owner stopped the motor to collect fares, the newspaper said.
   All the passengers were from the village of Pajukukang, about 80
miles south of the provincial capital of Ujung Pandang, it said.
</TEXT>
