<HEAD>Three Injured as Gunman In Car Fires Into Crowd At School</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ATLANTA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A gunman in a car fired a shotgun into a crowd
leaving a school talent show, wounding three people, authorities
said.
   The three victims, an adult and two teen-agers, were reported in
stable condition in area hospitals Saturday. They were hit in the
back, hand or legs.
   ``It was nothing but a drive-by, nothing but deranged
teen-agers,'' said Sylvester Carey, a chaperone. ``You can't try to
do anything nice for these kids, because someone will try to ruin
it.''
   The shooting at Southwest Middle School occurred Friday night as
about 500 people, mostly children, were leaving the school's talent
show.
   Police said they were looking for two cars that had been seen in
the area recently.
