and Friday, centered around the King William Hotel. A group of local
residents had sought to close the hotel months before the girl's
death, although its insist the hotel isn't a crack house.
   Police tried to close the hotel by getting it declared a public
nuisance. However, the hotel countersued, and the case is pending in
Chancery Court, a police spokesman said Saturday.
