<FIRST>r a AM-Iditarod     03-18 0157</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Iditarod,0160</SECOND>
<HEAD>Adkins Last to Qualify for Iditarod Money</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NOME, Alaska (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Terry Adkins of Sand Coulee, Mont., on Friday
became the last musher to qualify for a share of the $250,000 purse
in the Iditarod Trail Sled Dog Race.
   Adkins pulled into Nome at 3:14 p.m. to become the 20th finisher
in the annual 1,168-mile race from Anchorage. The purse is disbursed
among the top 20 mushers, with $50,000 going to the winner. Adkins
qualified for $3,000.
   Joe Runyan of Nenana won the Iditarod when he arrived in Nome on
Wednesday, after 11 days 5{ hours on the trail.
   Nineteen mushers continued pressing toward Nome after Adkins
arrived. Richard Self of Sterling, Diana Dronenburg of Willow; Jerry
Austin of St. Michael, Mitch Brazin of St. Michael; and Jamie Nelson
of Togo, Minn., were within 22 miles of Nome. The last musher,
Carolyn Muegge-Vaughan of Trapper Creek, was at Unalakleet, 267
miles from the finish.
</TEXT>
